title: Google\Cloud\Dialogflow\V2\ExportAgentRequest
name: ExportAgentRequest
description:
The request message for [Agents.ExportAgent][google.cloud.dialogflow.v2.Agents.ExportAgent].

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dialogflow.v2.ExportAgentRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The project that the agent to export is associated with. Format: projects/<Project ID>.

params.name: data.agent_uri
params.description: Required. The Google Cloud Storage URI to export the agent to. The format of this URI must be gs://<bucket-name>/<object-name>. If left unspecified, the serialized agent is returned inline. Dialogflow performs a write operation for the Cloud Storage object on the caller's behalf, so your request authentication must have write permissions for the object. For more information, see Dialogflow access control.
